abstract: Former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid on Wednesday said it was possible the crowded Democratic primary race was headed toward a contentious convention fight and downplayed the political dangers of a scenario many party leaders are dreading.
snippet: Former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid on Wednesday said it was possible the crowded Democratic primary race was headed toward a contentious convention fight and downplayed the political dangers of a scenario many party leaders are dreading.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid on Wednesday said it was possible the crowded Democratic primary race was headed toward a contentious convention fight and downplayed the political dangers of a scenario many party leaders are dreading.
headline_main: Harry Reid: Brokered Convention 'Not the End of the World'
headline_print_headline: Harry Reid: Brokered Convention 'Not the End of the World'

abstract: Democrats won’t commit to releasing the unofficial results of Saturday’s Nevada caucuses on the day of the vote, as they emphasize accuracy over speed in the aftermath of the chaos surrounding the Iowa caucuses.
snippet: Democrats won’t commit to releasing the unofficial results of Saturday’s Nevada caucuses on the day of the vote, as they emphasize accuracy over speed in the aftermath of the chaos surrounding the Iowa caucuses.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Democrats won’t commit to releasing the unofficial results of Saturday’s Nevada caucuses on the day of the vote, as they emphasize accuracy over speed in the aftermath of the chaos surrounding the Iowa caucuses.
headline_main: Democrats Won’t Commit to Same-Day Release of Nevada Results
headline_print_headline: Democrats Won’t Commit to Same-Day Release of Nevada Results

abstract: First Iowa, then New Hampshire. Now the president is on a Western trip, and basing it in Las Vegas, days before the Nevada caucuses.
snippet: First Iowa, then New Hampshire. Now the president is on a Western trip, and basing it in Las Vegas, days before the Nevada caucuses.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — President Trump is not exactly a fan of life on the road.

abstract: President Donald Trump trolled his political enemies Wednesday in the first of three rallies in three days in the West as Democrats vied in neighboring Nevada to be the one to challenge him in the November election.
snippet: President Donald Trump trolled his political enemies Wednesday in the first of three rallies in three days in the West as Democrats vied in neighboring Nevada to be the one to challenge him in the November election.
lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — President Donald Trump trolled his political enemies Wednesday in the first of three rallies in three days in the West as Democrats vied in neighboring Nevada to be the one to challenge him in the November election.
headline_main: At Arizona Rally, Trump Trolls Democrats Debating in Nevada
headline_print_headline: At Arizona Rally, Trump Trolls Democrats Debating in Nevada

abstract: Bernie Sanders says he doesn't plan to divulge additional information about his health, months after suffering a heart attack on the campaign trail and subsequently pledging to release “comprehensive” medical records.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bernie Sanders says he doesn't plan to divulge additional information about his health, months after suffering a heart attack on the campaign trail and subsequently pledging to release “comprehensive” medical records.
headline_main: Questions About Sanders' Health Linger After Heart Attack

abstract: Supporters of Senator Amy Klobuchar have also formed a super PAC. Both groups are now airing ads in Nevada.
snippet: Supporters of Senator Amy Klobuchar have also formed a super PAC. Both groups are now airing ads in Nevada.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Supporters of Senator Elizabeth Warren have formed a last-minute super PAC to boost her candidacy in Nevada and are plunging $1 million into television and other ads in the race’s final days, despite the Massachusetts senator’s previous outspoken opposition to such groups.

abstract: After he had a heart attack in October, Bernie Sanders said he would release ‘comprehensive’ medical records. But he has not done so.
snippet: After he had a heart attack in October, Bernie Sanders said he would release ‘comprehensive’ medical records. But he has not done so.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Ahead of a crucial Democratic debate on Wednesday night, Bernie Sanders is facing new pressure to release his full medical records, more than four months after he had a heart attack while campaigning and vowed he would provide “comprehensive” records on his health.
